content.text:
## CSS and HTML Diff Preview

### CSS Changes to fix z-index stacking and visibility:

```css
/* 1. Fix vioverse-app to be the background layer */
.vioverse-app {
    position: relative;
    width: 1920px;
    height: 1080px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background-color: #4f5a63;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 0; /* ADD: Ensure background is lowest layer */
}

/* 2. Fix report-canvas-container z-index */
.report-canvas-container {
    position: absolute;
    left: 360px;
    top: 129px;
    width: 810px;
    height: 920px;
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 0;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 1; /* ADD: Above background */
}

/* 3. Fix report-nav-bar z-index and positioning */
.report-nav-bar {
    position: absolute;
    left: 369px;
    top: 80px;
    width: 792px;
    height: 40px;
    background-color: #253541;
    border: 3px solid #9ba1a6;
    border-radius: 36px;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 2; /* ADD: Above canvas */
}

/* 4. Fix report-canvas z-index */
.report-canvas {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    position: relative;
    background-color: #ffffff;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 1; /* ADD: Ensure proper stacking */
}

/* 5. Fix viobox-container z-index */
.viobox-container {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 3; /* ADD: Above report canvas for overlays */
}

/* 6. Fix viobox visibility and interactivity */
.viobox {
    position: absolute;
    width: 557px;
    height: 26px;
    border: 2px solid var(--viobox-inactive);
    border-radius: 13px;
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    pointer-events: auto;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 4; /* ADD: Ensure vioboxes are interactive */
}

/* 7. Fix main-content and view-panel visibility */
.main-content {
    position: static;
    background: transparent;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: auto; /* ADD: Reset z-index */
}

.view-panel {
    width: 100%;
    display: none;
    position: relative; /* ADD: For proper stacking context */
}

.view-panel.active {
    display: block;
    z-index: auto; /* ADD: Reset z-index */
}

/* 8. Fix content-wrapper */
.content-wrapper {
    position: static;
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: auto; /* ADD: Reset z-index */
}
```

### Additional fixes for nav segments to ensure they're visible:

```css
/* Fix nav segment positioning within nav bar */
.nav-segment {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    height: 17px;
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    z-index: 1; /* ADD: Ensure segments are above nav bar background */
}

/* Fix nav arrows to be visible */
.nav-arrow-small {
    width: 17px;
    height: 17px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background-color: transparent;
    border: none;
    color: #9ba1a6;
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
    position: relative; /* ADD: For proper stacking */
    z-index: 2; /* ADD: Ensure clickable */
}

/* Fix nav dividers */
.nav-divider {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 18px;
    background-color: #9ba1a6;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    z-index: 0; /* ADD: Behind segments */
}
```

No HTML changes are needed - the issue is purely CSS z-index related.

