content.text:
## Analysis Summary:
- Nav bar is at left: 369px, top: 80px
- Report canvas is at left: 360px, top: 129px  
- Nav bar needs to align with canvas (left: 360px) and move up to be visually above it
- The navigation components are all present in the HTML, not missing

## CSS and HTML Diff Preview:

### CSS Changes:

```css
/* 1. Update report-canvas-container to be relatively positioned within the app */
.report-canvas-container {
    position: absolute;
    left: 360px;
    top: 129px;  /* Keep as is */
    width: 810px;
    height: 920px;
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 0;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 1;
}

/* 2. Fix report-nav-bar positioning to align with canvas */
.report-nav-bar {
    position: absolute;
    left: 360px;  /* Changed from 369px to align with canvas */
    top: 70px;    /* Changed from 80px to sit above canvas with proper spacing */
    width: 792px;
    height: 40px;
    background-color: #253541;
    border: 3px solid #9ba1a6;
    border-radius: 36px;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 2;
}

/* 3. Adjust segment positions to account for the nav bar shift */
/* Bureau segment */
.bureau-segment {
    position: absolute;
    left: 26px;  /* Adjusted from 17px (+9px) */
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
}

/* Date segment */
.date-segment {
    position: absolute;
    left: 177px;  /* Adjusted from 168px (+9px) */
    width: 134px;
}

/* Creditor segment */
.creditor-segment {
    position: absolute;
    left: 384px;  /* Adjusted from 375px (+9px) */
    width: 150px;
}

/* Page segment */
.page-segment {
    position: absolute;
    left: 609px;  /* Adjusted from 600px (+9px) */
    width: 62px;
}

/* 4. Adjust divider positions */
.nav-divider:nth-of-type(1) {
    left: 160px;  /* Adjusted from 151px (+9px) */
}

.nav-divider:nth-of-type(2) {
    left: 368px;  /* Adjusted from 359px (+9px) */
}

.nav-divider:nth-of-type(3) {
    left: 592px;  /* Adjusted from 583px (+9px) */
}

/* 5. Alternative approach: Position nav bar relative to canvas container */
/* This would require HTML structure change - moving nav bar inside canvas container */
```

### Alternative Approach (Recommended):
Move the nav bar to be a child of report-canvas-container and use relative positioning:

```css
/* Make report-canvas-container the positioning context */
.report-canvas-container {
    position: absolute;
    left: 360px;
    top: 129px;
    width: 810px;
    height: 920px;
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 0;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: visible; /* Changed from hidden to show nav bar above */
    z-index: 1;
}

/* Position nav bar relative to its container */
.report-nav-bar {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;      /* Relative to container */
    top: -59px;   /* Above the container (40px height + 19px spacing) */
    width: 792px;
    height: 40px;
    background-color: #253541;
    border: 3px solid #9ba1a6;
    border-radius: 36px;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: hidden;
    z-index: 2;
}
```

